  <li id="comment-3015" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/12/plain-jane-with-chickpeas/#comment-3015"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-10-29T00:51:25-04:00">Friday, October 29, 2010 at 12:51 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Juliann, this can definitely be made ahead and reheated, but I think the texture and appearance will be nicest if you make it the day of.  Plus, it&#39;s so quick to make!  It won&#39;t take up much of your day.  If it makes the job more appealing, you can trim and wash the greens the day before, so all you have to do is throw them in the pan on the day of.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
